src_text: Nsirhelelo wa mati
trg_text: Water security

src_text: Khabinete yi khense vanhu va Afrika-Dzonga eka ku landzelela swipimelo swa mati leswi tirhisiweke eka swiphemu swo karhi swa Joni, Tshwane na Ekurhuleni ku tshamisekisa ntalo wa vuhlayiselamat Madamu na vuhlayiselamati swi tshama swi ri ehansi ka ntshikelelo hikwalaho ka mahiselo ya le henhla eGauteng, naswona ku laviwa loku tlakukeke ku sindzise Rand Water ku hunguta mphakelo wa mati eka timasipala hi mpimo lowukul Vulawuri bya mati byi phakela mati yo nwa yo tala eka kutlula 11 wa timiliyoni ta vanhu eGauteng, swiphemu swa Mpumalanga, Free State na N'walungu-Vupeladyamb
trg_text: Cabinet thanked South Africans for adhering to water restrictions implemented in certain parts of Johannesburg, Tshwane and Ekurhuleni to stabilise the capacity of reservoir Dams and reservoirs remain under pressure due to high temperatures in Gauteng, and increasing demand forced Rand Water to reduce water supply to municipalities drasticall The water utility supplies bulk potable water to more than 11 million people in Gauteng, parts of Mpumalanga, the Free State and North Wes

src_text: Swipimelo leswo ka swi nga papalateki swi na xikongomelo xa ku sirhelela mphakelo wa mati naswona swi ta tshama swi ri kona kufikelaloko xiyimo lexi xi antsw Khabinete yi kombele vaaki ku landzelela swipimelo swa mati na ku tlanga xiphemu xa vona hi ku tirhisa xipfuno lexo kala hi switsongotsongo
trg_text: These unavoidable restrictions aim to secure water supply and will remain in place until the situation improve Cabinet called on the public to continue adhering to the water restrictions and play their part by using this scarce resource sparingly

src_text: itereko xa Transnet
trg_text: Transnet strike

src_text: Khabinete yi amukele ntwanano wa muholo wa malembe manharhu lowu fikeleriweke exikarhi ka Transnet na United National Transport Union (UNTU), lowu nga ta tirha eka nkarhi wa 1 Dzivamisoko 2022 kufika 31 Nyenyanyana 2025.
trg_text: Cabinet welcomed the three-year wage deal reached between Transnet and the United National Transport Union (UNTU), which is applicable for the period 1 April 2022 to 31 March 2025.

src_text: Khomixini ya Mbuyelelano, Vulamuri na Vuahluri yi lamurile eka ntwanano lowu, leswi swi fikiseke emakumu xitereko xa vatirhi hi swirho swa UNTU hi nkarhi wolow Khabinete yi tlhele yi amukela xiboho hi South African Transport and Allied Workers Union ku herisa xitereko lex
trg_text: The Commission for Conciliation, Mediation and Arbitration mediated this deal, which ended the current industrial action by members of UNTU with immediate effec Cabinet also welcomed the decision by the South African Transport and Allied Workers Union to call off the strik

src_text: Khabinete yi amukele vutiboheleri hi Transnet ku kongomisa eka ku hetisiwa ka mitirho leya saleleke endzhaku loku humeleleke eka mihlaluko na le swiporweni hi nkarhi wa xitereko xa vatirhi, leswi swi khumbeke hi ndlela yo homboloka ikhonomi na tisekitara leti ti tshembelaka eka vukorhokeri bya yon
trg_text: Cabinet welcomed the commitment by Transnet to focus on clearing backlogs that occurred across the port and rail system during the industrial action, which negatively impacted the economy and sectors that are dependent on its service

src_text: Khabinete yi hundzise ku khensa ka yona eka nseketelo na ntirhisano lowu nyikiweke hi bindzu hi nkarhi wa xitereko lex
trg_text: Cabinet expressed its gratitude to the support and cooperation given by business during the strik

src_text: Yi khutaza vuxaka lebyi yaka emahlweni exikarhi ka vufambisi na vatirhi va Transnet ku vuyerisa khamphani na ikhonomi ya tiko
trg_text: It encourages a continuous relationship between Transnet management and labour for the benefit of the company and the economy of the country

src_text: Vuxaka bya Afrika-Dzonga
trg_text: South Africa

src_text: Saudi Arabia
trg_text: Saudi Arabia relations

src_text: Khabinete yi amukele Rendzo ro Tirha leri humeleleke kuya eKingdom of Saudi Arabia hi Phuresidente Cyril Ramaphosa hi masiku ya 15 na 16 Nhlangula 2022.
trg_text: Cabinet welcomed the successful Working Visit to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia by President Cyril Ramaphosa on 15 and 16 October 2022.

src_text: Hi nkarhi wa rendzo leri, matiko lamambirhi ma sayine 17 wa Timemorandamu ta Ntwanano (tiMoU) eka tindzima to hambanahambana to tanihi vurimi, indasitiri ya tinhlampfi, vucelamigodi, eneji leyi vuyelerisekaka, nsirhelelo, vutleketli na swimila na swiharhi swa le lwandle ku endla swakudy TiMoU tin'wana leti sayiniweke ti hi mayelana na ku tumbuluxiwa ka Khansele ya Mabindzu ya Nhlanganelo, ntirhisano eka ndzima ya tiindasitiri ta swa nyimpi na maxavelo ya tinhundzu na vukorhokeri, na hi mayelana na ntirhisano wa mivalango ya ntivoxivumbekomisav
trg_text: During the visit, the two countries signed 17 Memoranda of Understanding (MoUs) in various fields such as agriculture, fisheries, mining, renewable energy, security, transport and aquacultur Other MoUs signed are on the establishment of a Joint Business Council, cooperation in the field of military industries and procurements, and on geological survey cooperatio

src_text: Phuresidente u tirhise rendzo leri ku rhamba mabindzu ya le Saudi Arabia kuya eka khomferense ya vuvekisi ya vuntlhanu ya Afrika-Dzonga leyi yi nga ta khomiwa hi 2023.
trg_text: The President used the visit to invite Saudi Arabia businesses to South Africa s fifth investment conference that will be held in 2023.

src_text: Saudi Arabia i mutirhisani lonkulu wa vumbirhi wa Afrika-Dzonga eVuxa-Xikarhi naswona i xihlovo lexikulu kutlula hinkwaswo xa switundziwa kusuka eka xifundza lex Vuxaka bya matiko ya misava exikarhi ka matiko hamambirhi byi vangile xitandzhaku eka mabindzu na maendlekelo ya vuvekisi
trg_text: Saudi Arabia is South Africa s second largest trading partner in the Middle East and the largest source of imports from the regio International relations between both countries have resulted in a positive effect on trade and investment trends

src_text: Vuvekisi bya switirhisiwakulu
trg_text: Infrastructure investment

src_text: Khabinete yi amukele ku endliwa ka pulanti ya vuhumesi bya tipulasitiki ya ximanguvalawa hi muendli wa matiko ya misava wo rhangela, ALPLA Group, eLanseria eGauten
trg_text: Cabinet welcomed the commissioning of a state-of-the-art plastics production plant by leading international manufacturer, the ALPLA Group, at Lanseria in Gauten

src_text: Leyi yi engetela vutiboheleri bya Phuresidente Ramaphosa ku veka nhluvukiso wa switirhisiwakulu eka xiyimo tanihi
trg_text: This augments President Ramaphosa s commitment to position infrastructure development as a means to stimulate the economy and increase employmen

src_text: ndlela ya ku hlohlotela ikhonomi na ku engetela mitirh
trg_text: capacity to process locally grown produc

src_text: Vuvekisi lebyi nga na nkoka wa US$50 wa timiliyoni i vuhoxaxandlakulu eka kungukulu ra Lanseria Smart City leri ri nga ta lawula vuyisekamahlweni na ku vuyelerisa switirhisiwa xikan'we na ku tumbuluxa na ku yisa emahlweni 350 wa mitirh Leswi swi katsiweke hi nongoloko wa vudyondzisantirho wa 36 wa timakhetironiki na van'wavuthekiniki vo vuyelerisa eka mitirho ya ALPLA Group eAfrika ya le dzongeni hinkway Nongoloko lowa vudyondzisantirho wu ta sungula hi 2023, ku ri na vadyondzisiwantirho va le Afrika-Dzonga va 12 lavo sungula lava humaka emigangeni ya kwala tikweni
trg_text: The investment worth US$50 million is a key contribution to the Lanseria Smart City masterplan that will drive sustainability and recycling as well as create and sustain 350 job Included is an apprenticeship programme for 36 mechatronics and recycling technicians for ALPLA Group operations across southern Afric The apprentice programme will commence in 2023, with the first 12 South African apprentices coming from local communities

src_text: Vucelamigodi lebyi nga riki enawini
trg_text: Illegal mining

src_text: Vucelamigodi lebyi nga riki enawini byi vavisa miganga na ikhonomi ya hina, naswona byi vanga ndzahleko wa malinhlengeleto eka havumbirhi bya mfumo na sekitara ya vucelamigod
trg_text: Illegal mining hurts communities and our economy, and results in a loss of revenue for both government and the mining secto

src_text: Khabinete yi amukele ku tekiwa ka xisaka xa swibalesa na ku khomiwa ka 20 wa vaehleketeleriwa lava xakelanisiweke na vucelamigodi lebyi nga riki enawini hi nkarhi wa oparexini emuhochweni wa mugodi eStilfontein eN'walungu-Vupeladyamb
trg_text: Cabinet welcomed the seizure of a firearms cache and the arrest of 20 suspects linked to illegal mining during an operation at a mineshaft in Stilfontein in North Wes

src_text: Khabinete yi kombela vanhu va le Afrika-Dzonga ku ya emahlweni va tirhisana na tiejensi ta nsindziso wa nawu ku tiyisisa ku humelela ka tioparexini to lwisana na vugevenga ta nkarhi lowu tak Leswi swi ta rhumela xihungwana xo tiya xa leswaku vugevenga a byi hakeli, na leswaku swigevenga swi ta khomiwa na ku tengisiwa ku ri hava nchavo kumbe ku rhandziw 6.
trg_text: Cabinet appeals to South Africans to continue working with law-enforcement agencies to ensure the success of future anti-crime operation This will send a strong message that crime does not pay, and that criminals will be arrested and prosecuted without fear or favou 6.

src_text: Eneji
trg_text: Energy

src_text: Eskom ya ha sayina mitwanano ya vulombisi bya 30 wa malembe na vavekisi va vahumesi va gezi lava tiyimelaka ku aka ntalo wo endla eneji yo basa wuntshwa eka switichi swa gezi swa Majuba na Tutuka eMpumalang Vulombisi lebya misava byi ta koka rinoko ra vuvekisi lebyi kumbeteriwaka bya kwalomu ka R40 wa tibiliyon
trg_text: Eskom recently signed 30-year lease agreements with four independent power producer investors to construct new clean-energy generation capacity at Majuba and Tutuka power stations in Mpumalang The land leases will attract an estimated investment of about R40 billio

trg_text: The new generation capacity is expected to be connected to the grid within 24 to 36 months from financial closure, subject to environmental, land zoning and other regulatory approvals

src_text: Nsirhelelo wa swakudya
trg_text: Food security

src_text: Khabinete yi amukele ku rhurheriwa ka Ntsombano wa Agri SA wa 2022 ePitori hi masiku ya 13 na 14 Nhlangula 2022 ehansi ka nkongomelo:
trg_text: Cabinet welcomed the hosting of the Agri SA Congress 2022 in Pretoria on 13 and 14 October 2022 under the theme:

src_text: Ku Rima swa laha Tikweni .
trg_text: Growing Local .

src_text: Ntsombano lowu vulavurisane hi mayelana na timhaka to tanihi ku endla ntirho wa makungukulu ya vurimi ya varimi va laha tikweni; switirhisiwakulu leswi yisekaka emahlweni eka swakudya leswi rimiweke laha tikweni; ku endliwa ka mbangu wa laha tikweni wu va lowu yisekaka emahlweni eka ntshovelo wa swakudya swa laha tikweni kuya eka nkarhi lowu taka, na ku tiyisiwa ka vuswikoti bya vatshoveri va swakudya ku phurosesa swirin'wa leswi rimiweke laha tikwen
trg_text: The congress engaged on issues such as making agriculture masterplans work for local growers; sustainable infrastructure for locally grown food; making the local environment sustainable for local food production into the future, and strengthening food producers

src_text: Eka ku rhangisiwa ku ya emahlweni ka nsirhelelo wa swakudya, Khabinete yi tlhele yi amukela ku simekiwa ka Habu ya Nsirhelelaswihanyi ya Rixaka hi Nongoloko wa Xinakulobye xa Vutumbuluxi bya Ikhonomiswihanyi ya Vurimi wa Ndzawulo ya Sayense na Vutumbuluxi, hi ku tirhisana na Yunivhesiti ya Pitor Habu leyi yi ta seketela nsivelo, hunguto na malawulelo ya vuvabyi bya swirin'wa na swiharhi, leswi swi nga ta hoxa xandla eka ntshovelo, nsirhelelo wa swakudya na nhluvukiso wa matikoxikaya lowu yisekaka emahlwen
trg_text: In further prioritising food security, Cabinet also welcomed the launch of the National Biosecurity Hub, by the Department of Science and Innovation's Agricultural Bio-economy Innovation Partnership Programme, in collaboration with the University of Pretori The hub will support the prevention, reduction and management of crop and animal disease, which will contribute to increased productivity, food security and sustainable rural developmen

src_text: Ku Pfumeleriwa Ximfumo ka Chatara ya Vuhangalasi bya Matimba ya Yuniyoni ya Afrika (AU)
trg_text: Ratification of the Decentralisation Charter of the African Union (AU)

src_text: Khabinete yi pasise xiringanyeto xo ya ePalamende xa Chatara ya AU hi mayelana na Mikhuvanene na Milawu ya Vuhangalasi bya Matimba, Mafumelo ya le Tikweni na Nhluvukiso wa le Tikweni ku ya pfumeleriwa ximfum Afrika-Dzonga yi sayine chatara leyi hi Mhawuri 2022.
trg_text: Cabinet approved the submission to Parliament the AU Charter on the Values and Principles of Decentralisation, Local Governance and Local Development for ratificatio South Africa signed the charter in August 2022.

src_text: Chatara ya Vuhangalasi bya Matimba yi nyika rimba eka matiko lama nga swirho hinkwawo dokhumente yo letela hi mayelana na vuhangalasi bya matimba na mitirho kusuka eka mfumo wa rixaka kuya eka swiyenge swa swin'wana swa mfum Chatara leyi yi tirhana ngopfungopfu na vuhangalasi bya vulawuri na mitirho, rimba ra mafumelo ya le tikweni na nhluvukiso wa le tikweni
trg_text: The Decentralisation Charter provides a framework to all member states a guiding document on the decentralisation of powers and functions from national to other spheres of governmen The charter deals largely with the decentralisation of authority and functions, local governance framework and local development

src_text: Khansele ya Vuhlayiseki bya le Swiporweni ya Matiko ya Misava ya Lembe na Lembe ya vu32 (IRSC)
trg_text: 32nd Annual International Railway Safety Council (IRSC)

src_text: Khabinete yi pasise ku rhurheriwa ka Nhlengeletano ya IRSC ya Lembe na Lembe ya vu32 eJoni kusuka 1 kufika 6 Nhlangula 2023 ehansi ka nkongomelo:
trg_text: Cabinet approved the hosting of the 32nd Annual IRSC Meeting in Johannesburg from 1 to 6 October 2023 under the theme:

src_text: Ku vumbiwa hi vuntshwa ka swiporo eka Misava leyi kanakanisaka .
trg_text: Reshaping railways in an uncertain World .

src_text: IRSC i foramu ya matiko ya misava leyi yi tisaka endhawini yin'we tiphurofexinali ta vuhlayiseki bya le swiporweni kusuka emisaveni hinkwayo ku cincanisa mitokoto ku endlela ku antswisa vuhlayiseki bya le swiporwen
trg_text: The IRSC is an international forum that brings together railway safety professionals from all over the world to exchange experiences so as to improve railway safet

src_text: Tanihi xirho xa IRSC, Mulawuri wa Vuhlayiseki bya le Swiporweni wa Afrika-Dzonga u rhurhele rohetelela foramu leyi hi 201
trg_text: As a member of the IRSC, South Africa s Railway Safety Regulator last hosted this forum in 201

src_text: Xiyimo xa 2 xa Kungu ra Switirhisiwakulu ra Rixaka ra Mpfapfarhuto ra 2050 (NIP 2050)
trg_text: Draft National Infrastructure Plan 2050 (NIP 2050) Phase 2

src_text: Khabinete yi pasise ku gazetiwa ka Xiyimo xa 2 xa NIP ya 2050 ya mpfapfarhuto leswaku vaaki va nyika mavonel
trg_text: Cabinet approved the gazetting of the draft NIP 2050 Phase 2 for public consultatio

src_text: Kungu leri ri nyika mafambelo eka ku tiyisa na ku engetela tiphurojeke leti pfanganisiweke ta xiqhinga ta mfum
trg_text: The plan offers direction in strengthening and augmenting government strategic integrated project

src_text: Ri kuma tiphurojeke ta xiqhinga eka matshamelo ya vanhu; gezi ra masipala; mati; thyaka ro tiya; vutleketli bya mani na mani; switirhisiwakulu swa dyondzo na swa rihanyo; switirhisiwakulu swa xidijitali, na vugevenga na vukungundzwan
trg_text: It identifies the strategic projects in human settlements; municipal electricity; water; solid waste; passenger transport; education and health infrastructure; digital infrastructure, and crime and corruptio

src_text: Xivumbeko xa kungu leri xi nyika xivono xa xiyenge lexi ku faneleke ku tirhaniwa na xona, xi nyika nhlahluvo wa xiyimo xa nkarhi wa sweswi, xi katsakanya swiyimo swa nkoka swa ku humelela naswona xi vula leswaku i swidingo swihi leswi swi faneleke ku endliwa ku kota ku fikelela xivono lex Xi ringanyeta phurosese ya matirhiselo leyi yi fanele ku tekiwa eka kungu ra matirhelo ra ndzhendzeleko lowu yaka emahlweni wa malembe manharhu
trg_text: The format of the plan provides a vision of the area to be tackled, offers an assessment of the current status, outlines the essential conditions for success and states what needs to be done to achieve the visio It proposes the implementation process to be taken over the three-year running cycle action plan

src_text: Rimba ra Matirhiselo ra Rixaka eka Ku Endliwa ka Xiphurofexinali ka Vukorhokeri bya Mfumo
trg_text: National Implementation Framework towards the Professionalisation of the Public Service

src_text: Khabinete yi pasise Rimba ra Matirhiselo ra Rixaka eka Ku Endliwa ka Xiphurofexinali ka Vukorhokeri bya Mfum Rimba leri ri kandziyisiwile leswaku vaaki va nyika mavonelo hi 2021.
trg_text: Cabinet approved the National Implementation Framework towards the Professionalisation of the Public Servic The framework was published for public consultation in 2021.

src_text: Rimba leri ri nyika ntlhanu wa tiphuphu hi mayelana na miphalalo eka ku endliwa ka xiphurofexinali ka Vukorhokeri bya Mfum Tiphuphu leti ti katsa leswi endliwaka ku nga si thoriwa na ku hlawuriwa endzeni ka Vukorhokeri bya Mfumo; ku tivisiwa ka mutirhi na ku amukeriwa ka mutirhi entirhweni; nkunguhato na malawulelo ya matirhelo; ku dyondza loku yaka emahlweni na nhluvukiso wa xiphurofexinali, ku ya emahlweni ka ntirhovutomi na timhangu ta ntirhovutomi
trg_text: The framework provides five pillars on interventions in professionalising the Public Servic The pillars include pre-entry recruitment and selection within the Public Service; induction and onboarding; planning and performance management; continuous learning and professional development, and career progression and career incidents

src_text: Ku cinca eka swipimelo swa le ntirhweni swa Valawuri-Jenerala (tiDG)
trg_text: Changes in the conditions of employment for Directors-General (DGs)

src_text: Khabinete yi pasise xiviko lexi xi ringanyetaka magoza ku tiyisa vuswikoti bya tiDG eka Vukorhokeri bya Mfum Xiviko lexi xi endle swiringanyeto swo talanyana, ku katsa na nkarhi wa ku va ehofisini wa tiDG na malawulelo ya vurhumisi hi Vulawuri bya Vurhangerinkulu eka vaofisiri va tinkot
trg_text: Cabinet approved the report that proposes measures to strengthen the capacity and capability of the DGs in the Public Servic The report made several proposals,

src_text: Xiviko lexi xi tlhele xi ringanyeta leswaku DG ya le Hofisini ya Phuresidente yi ta thoriwa tanihi Nhloko ya Mafambiselo ya Mfum Eka swifundzakulu, ntirho lowu wu ta nyikiwa tiDG leri nga etihofisini ta Tiphurimiy Xiviko xi ye emahlweni xi ringanyeta magoza ku letela tindzawulo hi mayelana na malawulelo ya tikontiraka ta tiD
trg_text: The report also proposed that the DG in The Presidency will be designated as the Head of Public Administratio In the provinces, this function will be designated to the DGs in the offices of the Premier The report further proposed measures to guide departments on the management of contracts of DG

src_text: Sisiteme ya Malawulelo ya Matirhelo leyi pfuxetiweke ya tiDG yi le ku pfuxetiweni ku yi fambelanisa na ku cinca loku pasisiwek Holobye wo Khomela wa Vukorhokeri bya Mfumo na Mafambiselo, Ttn Thulas Nxesi, vhiki leri taka u ta rhamba nhlengeletano ya swihangalasamahungu ku hlamusela hi ku komisa Rimba ra Matirhiselo ra Rixaka eka ku Endliwa ka Xipfurofexinali ka Vukorhokeri bya Mfumo na ku tlhela a tlhantlha ku cinca ku loku pasisiweke eka swipimelo swa le ntirhweni swa tiDG
trg_text: The Acting Minister of Public Service and Administration, Mr Thulas Nxesi, will next week convene a media briefing to outline the National Implementation Framework towards the Professionalisation of the Public Service and also unpack the approved changes in the conditions of employment for DGs

src_text: Xiviko xa Ndzima leyi Khatsiweke xa Vuntlhanu hi mayelana na Matirhiselo ya Phepha ra Swibumabumelo ra Mfumo hi mayelana na Vanhu lava nga na Vutsoniwa (WPRPD) ra 2020-2021
trg_text: Fifth Progress Report on the Implementation of the White Paper on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (WPRPD) 2020-2021 Cabinet approved the Fifth Progress Report on the Implementation of the WPRPD, which provides an update on the implementation of the WPRP The report covers inputs from national and provincial government department It provides updates on the policy implementation that include budget allocation

src_text: Khabinete yi pasise Xiviko xa Ndzima leyi Khatsiweke xa Vuntlhanu hi mayelana na Matirhiselo ya WPRPD, lexi xi nyikaka vuxokoxoko byintshwa hi mayelana na matirhiselo ya WPRP Xiviko lexi xi angarhela swibumabumelo kusuka eka tindzawulo ta mfumo ta rixaka na ta swifundzakul Xi nyika vuxokoxoko byintshwa hi mayelana na matirhiselo ya pholisi lama ma katsaka miavelo ya mpimanyet
trg_text: The MTBPS gives substance to government's commitments within an overall level of spending that the nation can affor It further details how government will close the gap between revenue and expenditure, and make the most of the available resource 5.

src_text: Xiviko xa ku ya emahlweni xa lembe na lembe xo sungula xi kandziyisiwile hi 2017.
trg_text: The first annual progress report was published in 2017.

src_text: Xiviko xa ndzima leyi khatsiweke xa vuntlhanu xi pasisiwile ku va xi gazetiwa na ku kandziyisiwa hi Ndzawulo ya Vavasati, Vantshwa na Vanhu lava nga na Vutsoniwa
trg_text: This fifth progress report has been approved to be gazetted and published by the Department of Women, Youth and Persons with Disabilities

src_text: Hundzuluxo eka Atikili ya 20(1) ya Ntwanano hi mayelana na ku Herisiwa ka Mixaka Hinkwayo ya Xihlawuhlawu Ehenhla ka Vavasati (CEDAW)
trg_text: Amendment to Article 20(1) of the Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW)

src_text: Khabinete yi pasise xiringanyeto xo ya ePalamende xa hundzuluxo wa Atikili ya 20(1) ya CEDAW leswaku wu ya pfumeleriwa ximfum Mihundzuluxo leyi yi lulamisela nkarhivunavi lowu engeteriweke wa tinhlengeletano ta komiti leti ti phurosesaka swiviko swa matiko lama nga swirh
trg_text: Cabinet approved the submission to Parliament of the amendment to Article 20(1) of the CEDAW for ratificatio The amendments provide for an increased duration of the committee meetings that process the member states

src_text: Afrika-Dzonga yi sayine ntwanano lowu hi 1993 kutani endzhakukaswona yi wu pfumelela ximfumo hi N'wendzamhala 1995.
trg_text: South Africa signed this convention in 1993 and subsequently ratified it in December 1995.

src_text: Xiringanyeto lexo ya ePalamende xi lava ku fambelanisa ntwanano lowu pfumeleriweke ximfumo nkarhi lowu nga hundza na hundzuluxo wa Atikili ya 20(1) ya ntwanano lowu
trg_text: The submission to Parliament seeks to align the previously ratified convention with the amendment to Article 20(1) of the convention

src_text: Ntwanano wa Misava Hinkwayo hi mayelana na ku Tekeriwa Enhlokweni ka Mithwaso leyi khumbaka Dyondzo ya le Henhla
trg_text: Global Convention on the Recognition of Qualifications concerning Higher Education

src_text: Khabinete yi pasise xiringanyeto xo ya Palamende xa Ntwanano wa Misava Hinkwayo hi mayelana na ku Tekeriwa Enhlokweni ka Mithwaso leyi khumbaka Dyondzo ya le Henhl Xikan'wekan'we loko xi pasisiwile ximfumo xi ta nghenisiwa eka Nhlangano wa Dyondzo, Sayense na Mfumo wa Vun'we bya Tinxaka (UN) kutani laha tikweni xi ta endliwa xi tirha hi ku tirhisa Nawu wa Rimba ra Mithwaso wa Rixaka, 2008 (Nawu wa 67 wa 2008).
trg_text: Cabinet approved the submission to Parliament of the Global Convention on the Recognition of Qualifications concerning Higher Education for ratificatio Once ratified it will be deposited to the United Nations (UN) Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization and domestically enabled through the National Qualifications Framework Act, 2008 (Act 67 of 2008).

trg_text: National Presidential Small, Micro and Medium Enterprises (SMME) and Cooperatives Summit

src_text: Ndzawulo ya Nhluvukiso wa Mabindzu Lamatsongo, hi ku tirhisana na vakhomaxiave va sekitara leyi nga riki ya mfumo, yi ta rhurhela Samiti ya SMME na Mabindzunhlanganelo ya Phuresidente eBryanston, Gauteng kusuka 13 kufika 15 Hukuri 2022.
trg_text: The Department of Small Business Development, in partnership with private-sector stakeholders, will host the National Presidential SMME and Cooperatives Summit in Bryanston, Gauteng from 13 to 15 November 2022.

src_text: Samiti leyi yi tisa endhawini yin'we vatlanginkulu va sekitara leyi nga riki ya mfumo na ya mfumo eka ikhosisiteme ya mabindzu lamatsongo, ku burisana hi mayelana na ku kuma tindlela ta ku tirhisana eka ku tiyisa sekitara ley Vatekaxiave lava languteriwaka va katsa tichembara ta mabindzu, vatirhi va SMME, swidyondzeki, vaendlatipholisi na mihlangano ya timali ya nhluvukis
trg_text: The summit will bring together private and public sector key actors in the small enterprise ecosystem, to deliberate on finding ways to collaborate in strengthening this secto Expected participants include chambers of commerce, SMME practitioners, academics, policymakers and development finance institution

src_text: Samiti leyi yi ta tlhela yi kanela Kungukulu ra Nhluvukiso wa mabindzu Lamatsongo leri Pfanganisiweke ra Rixaka, leri ri nyikaka rimba ra xiqhinga ku tiyisa sekitara ya SMM Samiti leyi yi tlhela yi languteriwa ku tivisa Masagwati ya SMME ya Phuresidente ya Rixaka ya Lembe na Lembe
trg_text: The summit will also discuss the National Integrated Small Enterprise Development Masterplan, which provides a strategic framework to strengthen the SMME secto The summit is also expected to introduce the Annual National Presidential SMME Awards
